                    <span>Neil Hayes took me places I didn't expect to go. What a fascinating portrait of a fascinating program. My brother is a coach in Southern California and I sent him this book because of the unique perspective it offers. It's amazing the wholesome culture that has been set up at De La Salle. Hayes does a great job of describing every facet of the football program. The secret to De La Salle's succes: Sure, they've started getting good talent, but they also work harder and take it more seriously than you could ever imagine.</span>
                  
              
